@sxjscience I am wondering that this problem may be caused by the channel sharing of the PReLU parameters. And I am trying to add the `channel_shared` parameter to the PReLU. However, I am encountering a problem to sum of the all elements. It seems that mshadow does not contain a `sumall` function. Will you give me some advice to how to implement the `sumall` function?

More specificly, https://github.com/dmlc/mxnet/blob/master/src/operator/leaky_relu-inl.h#L179-L180 is changed to:

```
if (!param_.channel_shared) {
  Assign(grad_weight, req[leakyrelu::kGamma], sumall_except_dim<1>(F<prelu_grad>(data) * grad));
  Assign(gdata, req[leakyrelu::kData],
    F<mshadow_op::xelu_grad>(output, broadcast<1>(weight, data.shape_)) * grad);
} else {
  Assign(grad_weight, req[leakyrelu::kGamma], sumall(F<prelu_grad>(data) * grad)); // sumall?
  Assign(gdata, req[leakyrelu::kData],
    F<mshadow_op::xelu_grad>(output, weight[0]) * grad); // broadcast<1>(weight, data.shape_)) * grad);
}
```

But how can I write the `sumall` function?

